201
00:14:40,346 --> 00:14:42,381
Damn, no, no!

202
00:14:42,381 --> 00:14:45,084
You'll never be able to create good broth if
you keep shaving dried fish like that.

203
00:14:45,084 --> 00:14:46,881
Shave them thicker!

204
00:14:47,286 --> 00:14:48,187
Yes, Sir.

205
00:14:48,187 --> 00:14:50,422
Why the hell do I need to do things like this?

206
00:14:50,422 --> 00:14:53,653
I was once called a genius bank robber.

207
00:14:57,196 --> 00:14:58,663
This is perfect!

208
00:14:59,665 --> 00:15:02,101
Hey, Ryo, don't you think it
might be a good idea

209
00:15:02,101 --> 00:15:03,869
to have some advertisement
for this restaurant?

210
00:15:03,869 --> 00:15:06,605
Yes, these times require advertisement.

211
00:15:06,605 --> 00:15:07,773
Shall we distribute flyers or something?

212
00:15:07,773 --> 00:15:08,741
No way.

213
00:15:08,741 --> 00:15:10,442
It seems like it's not working at all.

214
00:15:10,442 --> 00:15:11,610
Actually, we did it for our business,

215
00:15:11,610 --> 00:15:13,339
but Saeba Company doesn't have
any clients at all.

216
00:15:14,146 --> 00:15:15,613
Advertisement...

217
00:15:25,524 --> 00:15:27,685
No! How many times do I have to tell you?!

218
00:15:29,061 --> 00:15:30,729
What's the matter?

219
00:15:30,729 --> 00:15:33,365
I can quit doing this right now.

220
00:15:33,365 --> 00:15:36,335
Hey, man, aren't you too hard on her?

221
00:15:36,335 --> 00:15:38,270
It's okay, Ms. Kaori.

222
00:15:38,270 --> 00:15:39,737
It's all my fault.

223
00:15:40,873 --> 00:15:42,966
I'm sorry. I have to go shopping.

224
00:15:46,612 --> 00:15:48,047
She's out now.

225
00:15:48,047 --> 00:15:49,344
Good, get her!

226
00:15:59,591 --> 00:16:00,558
That voice!

227
00:16:03,395 --> 00:16:04,862
Sir!

228
00:16:05,564 --> 00:16:07,725
Oh, no! Mika's been kidnapped!

229
00:16:09,735 --> 00:16:14,297
I'm sorry, but I want you to sign a contract.

230
00:16:17,176 --> 00:16:20,270
It's that guy, the other man who
was at Shirako-Ya.

231
00:16:20,412 --> 00:16:21,379
What the hell?!

232
00:16:24,383 --> 00:16:25,850
Damn! Run over him!

233
00:16:44,403 --> 00:16:45,870
Get out of the car!

234
00:16:54,980 --> 00:16:56,277
Bastard!

235
00:17:03,989 --> 00:17:05,791
Can't you see this?

236
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:07,782
If you come any closer to me,
I'm gonna shoot her.

237
00:17:19,171 --> 00:17:21,240
Promise me.

238
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:23,208
You'll never ever even try to
contact Shirako-Ya.

239
00:17:23,876 --> 00:17:25,511
I promise!

240
00:17:25,511 --> 00:17:26,745
Please forgive me!

241
00:17:26,745 --> 00:17:28,113
Good boy.

242
00:17:28,113 --> 00:17:31,082
The next time I see you, you'll be dead.

243
00:17:32,684 --> 00:17:34,151
Yes, Sir!

244
00:17:35,754 --> 00:17:38,882
Mr. Saeba! I... I...

245
00:17:40,159 --> 00:17:41,460
Shall we go back?

246
00:17:41,460 --> 00:17:43,519
Everybody is waiting for your soba noodles.

247
00:17:44,096 --> 00:17:45,654
Mr. Saeba...

248
00:17:46,165 --> 00:17:48,395
Yes, I'll do my best!

249
00:17:58,243 --> 00:18:00,575
At last, this is the final test for Ms. Mika.

250
00:18:10,856 --> 00:18:12,891
Torakichi is late.

251
00:18:12,891 --> 00:18:15,018
He told me that he was going to
buy a pack of cigarettes.

252
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:26,237
Hello...

253
00:18:30,709 --> 00:18:31,643
This is headquarters.

254
00:18:31,643 --> 00:18:35,101
